12/06/2003
ZVORNIK, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- SFOR reported Wednesday (11 June) that it has collected large quantities of arms in the Zvornik region, as part of Operation Harvest. 
Soldiers with the Dutch Battalion found 20 rifles, 80 hand grenades, four rocket launchers and approximately 3,000 bullets in Karakaj and Zvornik on Tuesday. 
The next day they collected similar quantities and types of weapons in Zvornik, and said the more active part of the operation would begin next week there. 
(Onasa, BBC - 11/06/03)
